    "body": "@Mailaender: It used spark particles. See https://github.com/LipkeGu/TSIniFiles/blob/master/rules.ini#L8061 and https://github.com/LipkeGu/TSIniFiles/blob/master/rules.ini#L8191. WeldingPart was the part it was throwing (with randomized colors and velocities, the EC can be ignored because it was longer than the amount of frames they'd need to reach the ground and IIRC these particles just faded away imminently when reaching it) and WeldingSys controlled the effect (spawning 20 particles in each frame for 25 frames).\n\n@Marnador D2k already has dummy weapons to properly render the trike's firinganims. See https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/bleed/mods/d2k/weapons/smallguns.yaml#L162 for such a dummy implementation - you do not even need to specify a value within the damagewarhead. I also stated that you should have a lot of dummyweapons (Armament@dummy1, Armament@dummy2 up to, say, 10) because yes, you cannot fire a weapon twice during the same frame.\n"
  },
